Vice President Mike Pence will join President Moon Jae-in of South Korea on June 30th to honor the veterans of the Korean War. They will participate in a wreath-laying ceremony at the Korean War Veterans Memorial in Washington, DC. President Moon, Vice President Pence, and Tom Stevens, the President of the National Korean War Veterans Association, will lay three wreaths at the memorial. The event will be attended by Korean War veterans and their families and will end with a moment of silence.